      <para styleclass="Heading1">Indenting code</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Image Caption" style="font-style:normal;">Visual studio automatically formats your code, so that you have a clearer overview of your code, and which parts do what.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Image Caption" style="font-style:normal;">This only happens if you have set the Indenting option on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Tools-Options-Tabs" styleclass="Image Caption" style="font-style:normal;">Tabs page</link><text styleclass="Image Caption" style="font-style:normal;"> to &quot;Smart&quot;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Image Caption" style="font-style:normal;">The rules for the formatting are defined on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Tools-Options-Indentation" styleclass="Image Caption" style="font-style:normal;">Indentation page</link></para>
